HEADWORD: Danish
<hw>Dan"ish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Dane</er>.]</ety> <def>Belonging to the Danes, or to their language
or country.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>The language of the
Danes.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Danish dog</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>one of a
large and powerful breed of dogs reared in Denmark; -- called also
<altname>great Dane</altname>. See <xex>Illustration</xex> in
Appendix.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

